  "text_preview": "\"last week\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► LAST WEEK : The American Sign Language (ASL) sign for \"last week / past week\" The sign for LAST WEEK incorporates the sign for WEEK but as the dominant hand moves off the non-dominant palm it moves back over the shoulder. Sample sentence: last-WEEK HAWAII STATE LEGISLATURE PASSED BILL REQUIRE MOVIE theater-[act] PROVIDE OPEN CAPTION. Notes: NEXT-WEEK WEEK WEEK-[advanced] WEEKLY WEEKEND * Want to help support ASL University? It's easy : DONATE ( Thanks! ) * Another way to help is to buy something from Dr. Bill's \" Bookstore .\" * Want even more ASL resources? Visit the \" ASL Training Center ! \" (Subscription Extension of ASLU) * Also check out Dr. Bill's channel: www.youtube.com/billvicars You "
}
